## Workflow

This project follows the **agentic-engineering playbook**.
For agent-owned implementation, use `/work` as the default loop in `agentic-playbook/06-workflow-loop.md`.

`/work` authorizes a scoped branch, implementation, gates, self-QA evidence, reviews, report, metrics sidecar, commit, push, and a Ready PR after all required gates pass. It does not authorize merging, force-pushing, closing issues, bypassing hooks, or destructive database/infrastructure commands.

For manual phase control, use the lower-level loop:

1. Per-task spec (Given/When/Then + constraints + examples) — see `templates/spec.template.md`
2. Plan-first (use `/plan`) — wait for human approval before code
3. Implement
4. Self-QA: `pnpm checks`
5. Anti-overengineering review: `/review`
6. PR body via `/pr`

Skills available: `/linearize`, `/work`, `/setup-quality`, `/plan`, `/implement`, `/review`, `/pr`, `/decompose`, `/bootstrap`, `/spec`, `/worktree`, `/cleanup-worktree`.
Subagents available: `planner`, `anti-overeng-reviewer`, `decomposer`, `pr-author`.

When you need user input, use the question tool if available. Do not ask for decisions in plain prose when a structured question tool exists.

